The park covers an area of 20,024 ha of well-preserved Atlantic Rain Forest (see 
Veloso et al. 1991
for more on local vegetation) and is located ca. 100 km from Rio de Janeiro, in a mountainous area ranging from 80 m to 2263 m elevation. The climate is tropical, with a colder drier season from May to August, and a rainy warmer period from November to February (
Flinte et al. 2009b
). Mean annual temperature is around 18 °C, maximum of 38 °C and minimum of 0 °C. Annual precipitation varies between 1250 and 1500 mm (
Flinte et al. 2008
).

